A vintage 1950s propaganda poster style illustration depicting a frantic figure in a rumpled business suit juggling multiple alarm clocks and stopwatches while running chaotically through a serene zen garden, trampling carefully raked sand patterns. The panicked figure leaves a trail of disruption behind them as calm meditating figures in the background look on with mild disapproval. The color palette features muted teals, burnt oranges, and cream tones typical of mid-century commercial art. The composition emphasizes the contrast between manufactured chaos and deliberate tranquility, with dynamic motion lines around the rushing figure against the peaceful geometric patterns of the garden.
